        <num>CC 806</num>
        <heading>806.  Expenses of maintenance and management</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 806.  Expenses of maintenance and management
A co-owner who on account of the thing held in indivision has incurred necessary expenses, expenses for ordinary maintenance and repairs, or necessary management expenses paid to a third person, is entitled to reimbursement from the other co-owners in proportion to their shares.
If the co-owner who incurred the expenses had the enjoyment of the thing held in indivision, his reimbursement shall be reduced in proportion to the value of the enjoyment.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
